1
00:01:00,625 --> 00:01:02,125
When people finish their day

2
00:01:02,502 --> 00:01:04,672
and hurry home,

3
00:01:05,818 --> 00:01:07,278
my day starts.

4
00:01:31,570 --> 00:01:33,860
My diner opens from midnight

5
00:01:34,463 --> 00:01:35,663
to seven in the morning.

6
00:01:37,198 --> 00:01:40,028
They call it "Midnight Diner."

7
00:01:42,101 --> 00:01:43,664
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

8
00:01:43,664 --> 00:01:45,742
That's all I have on my menu.
PORK MISO SOUP COMBO
BEER, SAKE, SHOCHU

9
00:01:45,953 --> 00:01:48,585
But I make whatever customers request

10
00:01:48,898 --> 00:01:51,065
as long as I have ingredients for it.

11
00:01:51,202 --> 00:01:52,782
That's my policy.

12
00:01:57,867 --> 00:01:59,370
Do I even have customers?

13
00:01:59,800 --> 00:02:01,340
More than you would expect.

14
00:02:04,243 --> 00:02:07,055
MIDNIGHT DINER:
TOKYO STORIES

15
00:02:07,056 --> 00:02:12,378
SOUR PLUM & PLUM WINE

16
00:02:30,084 --> 00:02:31,884
That's so annoying.

17
00:02:36,999 --> 00:02:39,829
I love this.

18
00:02:40,834 --> 00:02:43,956
- Dark beer?
- It's black cider.

19
00:02:44,546 --> 00:02:46,506
A friend in Toyama sent it to me.

20
00:02:46,811 --> 00:02:49,441
It's soy-sauce based
with some pepper. It's good.

21
00:02:52,495 --> 00:02:53,535
Thank you.

22
00:02:58,247 --> 00:03:00,707
How do you make a living
by selling these things?

23
00:03:01,690 --> 00:03:03,784
Ah, not so bad!

24
00:03:05,055 --> 00:03:07,475
What do you do during the winter?

25
00:03:09,302 --> 00:03:11,632
I sell some other stuff.

26
00:03:49,890 --> 00:03:51,347
Are you okay, boss?

27
00:03:51,847 --> 00:03:53,693
Yeah, I'm okay.

28
00:04:01,451 --> 00:04:03,098
What was wrong with him?

29
00:04:03,099 --> 00:04:05,559
He didn't look so sharp.

30
00:04:08,680 --> 00:04:09,510
Welcome.

31
00:04:14,487 --> 00:04:15,867
This is unusual.

32
00:04:16,103 --> 00:04:17,273
Here on a week night?

33
00:04:19,024 --> 00:04:20,944
I can't sleep.

34
00:04:22,446 --> 00:04:24,026
Shochu on the rocks, please.

35
00:04:24,646 --> 00:04:25,776
Anything to eat?

36
00:04:26,289 --> 00:04:28,619
Just... sour plum.

37
00:04:29,951 --> 00:04:30,791
Just one?

38
00:04:32,481 --> 00:04:33,311
Two.

39
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:41,485
Here you go.

40
00:04:46,445 --> 00:04:47,275
Thank you.

41
00:04:51,634 --> 00:04:54,384
Mr. Hoshino owns a produce store
in this neighborhood.

42
00:04:54,818 --> 00:04:58,538
All the vegetables I use here,
I buy from him.

43
00:05:05,883 --> 00:05:06,963
It's just not right.

44
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:09,182
What isn't?

45
00:05:10,487 --> 00:05:13,132
You bought this plum
from my store, didn't you?

46
00:05:13,132 --> 00:05:16,026
Yes. It's Nankobai from Kishu.

47
00:05:18,912 --> 00:05:22,292
Even if you use the same plums,
they're just not the same.

48
00:05:22,848 --> 00:05:23,968
What's the matter?

49
00:05:26,367 --> 00:05:29,417
My mother's sour plums finally ran out.

50
00:05:30,084 --> 00:05:31,294
I ate all of them.

51
00:05:32,651 --> 00:05:33,491
I see.

52
00:05:35,084 --> 00:05:35,914
When did she...

53
00:05:36,995 --> 00:05:38,285
pass away?

54
00:05:38,540 --> 00:05:39,660
Almost four years ago.

55
00:05:40,918 --> 00:05:42,668
That long?

56
00:05:45,561 --> 00:05:49,249
I knew they would run out someday
if I kept eating them every day.

57
00:05:49,250 --> 00:05:51,159
But when I'm drinking alone at home,

58
00:05:51,898 --> 00:05:53,710
I just get awfully lonely.

59
00:05:53,710 --> 00:05:55,790
I can't help eating one, or two.

60
00:05:57,698 --> 00:06:00,948
That's because I lived with my mother
for a long time.

61
00:06:03,730 --> 00:06:06,190
I pickle the plums myself every year.

62
00:06:07,189 --> 00:06:10,269
But they just won't turn out
like my mother's.

63
00:06:12,056 --> 00:06:14,019
Only your mother knows...

64
00:06:14,773 --> 00:06:16,313
just how much salt to use.

65
00:06:18,805 --> 00:06:19,894
The perfect amount.

66
00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:21,790
It's very important.

67
00:06:25,918 --> 00:06:30,218
When the sour plums ran out,
it really sank in that she was gone.

68
00:06:32,254 --> 00:06:34,344
That I really am alone now.

69
00:06:38,587 --> 00:06:39,667
These days...

70
00:06:39,961 --> 00:06:43,341
I feel that time passes faster
than before.

71
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:51,485
Master,

72
00:06:51,485 --> 00:06:52,315
just one more.

73
00:06:53,517 --> 00:06:55,948
Are you sure?
You have to wake up early tomorrow.

74
00:06:55,948 --> 00:06:57,884
Yes. Wake up at 4:30.

75
00:07:12,087 --> 00:07:13,957
Here you go.

76
00:07:15,250 --> 00:07:17,540
Was the produce store owner
hospitalized?

77
00:07:18,086 --> 00:07:19,636
Early stage diabetes.

78
00:07:19,986 --> 00:07:22,496
He has to be in the hospital
for two weeks.

79
00:07:23,012 --> 00:07:24,842
- Did you pay him a visit?
- Yeah.

80
00:07:25,452 --> 00:07:27,582
The owner of Kotodama
knew his hospital.

81
00:07:28,966 --> 00:07:30,476
Since his mother passed away,

82
00:07:30,908 --> 00:07:32,868
I bet he didn't eat too well.

83
00:07:33,882 --> 00:07:35,972
He never helped with chores.

84
00:07:36,302 --> 00:07:40,932
He said he feels like he's paying
for all the time he was being lazy now.

85
00:07:42,925 --> 00:07:43,845
Take care.

86
00:07:49,424 --> 00:07:50,344
Mr. Hoshino.

87
00:07:51,434 --> 00:07:52,934
Done with today's tests?

88
00:07:55,618 --> 00:07:56,498
Mr. Hoshino?

89
00:07:57,819 --> 00:08:01,989
An elderly woman always sat there
at this time of the day.

90
00:08:03,211 --> 00:08:04,721
Why isn't she here today?

91
00:08:06,706 --> 00:08:08,826
She was discharged
from the hospital.

92
00:08:24,580 --> 00:08:27,854
Why do we eat tokoroten with a chopstick?

93
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:29,820
Is this some kind of superstition?

94
00:08:30,241 --> 00:08:31,425
I'm not sure,

95
00:08:31,656 --> 00:08:35,196
but this is supposed to be
the most fashionable way to eat it.

96
00:08:35,634 --> 00:08:37,552
In the old days,

97
00:08:37,553 --> 00:08:40,723
they ate it with a long toothpick
like eating sweets.

98
00:08:42,409 --> 00:08:43,610
In Kansai Region,

99
00:08:43,611 --> 00:08:45,361
they eat it with brown sugar syrup.

100
00:08:48,842 --> 00:08:49,682
Welcome.

101
00:08:50,443 --> 00:08:51,273
Hello.

102
00:08:53,245 --> 00:08:55,795
Master, thank you for visiting me
at the hospital.

103
00:08:56,290 --> 00:08:59,510
We all were worried about you.
How's your diabetes?

104
00:08:59,937 --> 00:09:01,517
It's under control.

105
00:09:03,808 --> 00:09:06,224
But recently I can't sleep well.

106
00:09:06,224 --> 00:09:08,771
It has been extremely hot, that's why.

107
00:09:08,772 --> 00:09:10,362
Well, that's one reason, but...

108
00:09:12,004 --> 00:09:15,214
You see someone die in the hospital
every day.

109
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:19,780
I couldn't help thinking about myself
at night and got uneasy.

110
00:09:21,281 --> 00:09:22,737
I have no family.

111
00:09:22,918 --> 00:09:26,323
I must wonder who will take care
of my stuff after I die.

112
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:28,149
When we die, we die.

113
00:09:28,698 --> 00:09:31,036
Don't worry about
what happens afterwards.

114
00:09:31,036 --> 00:09:33,186
Why don't you get married?

115
00:09:33,186 --> 00:09:35,646
Find someone who is tough enough
to outlive you.

116
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:40,410
- I can't take this.
- What are you talking about?

117
00:09:42,409 --> 00:09:43,819
After I die...

118
00:09:44,737 --> 00:09:47,784
all the porn DVDs I have stored away
will be found.

119
00:09:47,784 --> 00:09:51,525
Then throw them away.
You are not a teenager anymore.

120
00:09:51,526 --> 00:09:54,259
That's not easy.

121
00:09:54,259 --> 00:09:55,792
Some are very rare items.

122
00:09:59,377 --> 00:10:00,417
Listen Master,

123
00:10:00,995 --> 00:10:03,995
if you came to my store
and found me dead...

124
00:10:05,542 --> 00:10:07,002
will you sneak into my house

125
00:10:07,327 --> 00:10:08,612
and throw them away secretly?

126
00:10:09,345 --> 00:10:10,401
What?

127
00:10:10,604 --> 00:10:13,948
You're single, too.
You understand, right?

128
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:17,850
Let's conclude a gentlemen's agreement.

129
00:10:20,280 --> 00:10:21,450
Master,

130
00:10:22,112 --> 00:10:24,793
please. I beg you.

131
00:10:24,793 --> 00:10:26,120
That's stupid.

132
00:10:27,058 --> 00:10:31,148
You can't get rid of your worldly passions
until you die, huh?

133
00:10:50,023 --> 00:10:53,693
Please open it.

134
00:10:59,468 --> 00:11:00,308
Who are you?

135
00:11:01,824 --> 00:11:04,664
Please open it.

136
00:11:06,225 --> 00:11:10,355
Please let me in.

137
00:11:12,337 --> 00:11:15,097
Yoichi...

138
00:11:16,493 --> 00:11:17,417
Mother?

139
00:11:18,153 --> 00:11:20,035
Please open it.

140
00:11:20,036 --> 00:11:23,755
Yoichi...

141
00:11:23,756 --> 00:11:28,636
please let me in.

142
00:11:31,038 --> 00:11:32,081
Mother,

143
00:11:32,457 --> 00:11:34,667
you are dead.

144
00:11:36,123 --> 00:11:40,633
I'm dead. That's why I'm asking you.

145
00:11:42,975 --> 00:11:46,467
Please let me in.

146
00:11:46,467 --> 00:11:48,387
Please.

147
00:11:50,643 --> 00:11:51,563
Mother,

148
00:11:53,043 --> 00:11:54,713
please rest in peace.

149
00:11:57,081 --> 00:11:57,921
Excuse me.

150
00:12:01,024 --> 00:12:01,944
Excuse me.

151
00:12:06,198 --> 00:12:07,914
Oh. Yes.

152
00:12:09,157 --> 00:12:10,407
I will take this.

153
00:12:16,008 --> 00:12:17,479
Isn't it damaged?

154
00:12:21,159 --> 00:12:22,517
Ah, this one, huh?

155
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,520
Every night in the last few days,

156
00:12:30,853 --> 00:12:32,393
while I am asleep,

157
00:12:33,104 --> 00:12:35,206
my dead mother comes and calls me.

158
00:12:35,206 --> 00:12:37,018
"Please open it."

159
00:12:37,018 --> 00:12:38,760
"Please let me in."

160
00:12:39,278 --> 00:12:40,528
She talks to me.

161
00:12:41,288 --> 00:12:43,958
Boss, you must have been dreaming.

162
00:12:45,736 --> 00:12:48,906
If I recite Buddhist scriptures,
under the blanket...

163
00:12:49,512 --> 00:12:52,012
she becomes sad and says,

164
00:12:53,448 --> 00:12:55,579
"Please let me in..."

165
00:12:55,579 --> 00:12:57,909
"I forgot something."

166
00:12:59,066 --> 00:13:00,026
Forgot something?

167
00:13:01,151 --> 00:13:03,948
She may be still keeping
her secret savings.

168
00:13:03,948 --> 00:13:06,959
I agree. She is worried about it.

169
00:13:06,960 --> 00:13:08,710
I don't think so.

170
00:13:09,479 --> 00:13:12,761
She put her entire fortune in a bag
and gave it to me

171
00:13:12,786 --> 00:13:14,371
before she died.

172
00:13:15,416 --> 00:13:18,126
Why don't you let her in?

173
00:13:19,694 --> 00:13:20,564
But...

174
00:13:21,383 --> 00:13:22,995
Even if she is my mother,

175
00:13:23,265 --> 00:13:24,395
she's a ghost.

176
00:13:25,241 --> 00:13:28,081
There is a line that shouldn't be crossed.

177
00:13:31,615 --> 00:13:33,405
- Good evening.
- Welcome.

178
00:13:35,744 --> 00:13:37,845
I thought that it might be ready.

179
00:13:38,041 --> 00:13:42,069
- I mean your plum wine.
- You are right.

180
00:13:42,257 --> 00:13:44,507
- Your plum wine?
- Yes.

181
00:13:44,946 --> 00:13:47,205
I make a big bottle of it every year.

182
00:13:47,498 --> 00:13:49,917
Summer is hot and I don't like it.

183
00:13:49,917 --> 00:13:51,799
But I can enjoy his plum wine.

184
00:13:52,435 --> 00:13:53,661
Who wants some?

185
00:13:53,661 --> 00:13:55,283
It's a year old, the perfect age.

186
00:13:55,502 --> 00:13:57,119
Yes!

187
00:14:01,765 --> 00:14:05,225
- Is your heart okay?
- It's not working.

188
00:14:06,219 --> 00:14:08,559
So she is worried about this, huh?

189
00:14:09,653 --> 00:14:13,323
My mother also made plum wine
whenever she salted plums.

190
00:14:14,147 --> 00:14:15,777
She loved it.

191
00:14:16,804 --> 00:14:19,514
I thought that she had finished it all.

192
00:14:20,820 --> 00:14:23,570
- Want a glass?
- No, thanks.

193
00:14:24,134 --> 00:14:27,844
- I don't want to upset your mother.
- Don't worry.

194
00:14:28,291 --> 00:14:31,751
I offered a glass of it at the altar.
Besides...

195
00:14:31,890 --> 00:14:35,150
today is the anniversary
of my mother's death.

196
00:14:36,057 --> 00:14:37,677
Please have some in her memory.

197
00:14:38,491 --> 00:14:39,741
Okay.

198
00:14:40,835 --> 00:14:42,335
I'll have just one glass.

199
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:45,680
Then me, too.

200
00:14:46,263 --> 00:14:48,665
Then can I have one, too?

201
00:14:50,151 --> 00:14:51,701
I love Master's,

202
00:14:52,665 --> 00:14:56,675
this one is also flavorful,
but mild at the same time.

203
00:14:57,385 --> 00:14:58,385
That's how

204
00:14:58,910 --> 00:15:02,160
they consumed all of it
after making an excuse.

205
00:15:02,688 --> 00:15:03,858
On that night...

206
00:15:05,636 --> 00:15:07,766
Yoichi...

207
00:15:09,434 --> 00:15:15,026
Yoichi...

208
00:15:15,929 --> 00:15:20,626
Yoichi...

209
00:15:22,764 --> 00:15:25,094
So it wasn't the plum wine?

210
00:15:48,741 --> 00:15:51,451
If it's not the plum wine,
then what else could it be?

211
00:15:56,195 --> 00:15:57,905
His mother wants to take him.

212
00:15:58,735 --> 00:16:00,985
If he crosses the Styx, he will be dead.

213
00:16:02,572 --> 00:16:03,492
What's this about?

214
00:16:05,093 --> 00:16:06,893
The produce store owner.

215
00:16:07,694 --> 00:16:11,024
A spirit of his dead mother
shows up every night

216
00:16:11,533 --> 00:16:12,783
and he can't sleep.

217
00:16:13,425 --> 00:16:16,925
I see. Does she have something to regret?

218
00:16:17,165 --> 00:16:18,705
We can't figure it out.

219
00:16:20,707 --> 00:16:23,757
Because of my trade,
I've seen a lot of ways to die.

220
00:16:24,136 --> 00:16:26,883
Die happily with nothing to regret?

221
00:16:26,884 --> 00:16:29,884
It's rare. Many have something to regret.

222
00:16:30,770 --> 00:16:33,400
But you all sound very unscientific.

223
00:16:34,873 --> 00:16:37,713
She forgot something
and wants to come in, right?

224
00:16:38,168 --> 00:16:40,038
Then it must be in the house.

225
00:16:40,739 --> 00:16:42,634
If that's the case,

226
00:16:42,875 --> 00:16:45,360
he should search the house thoroughly.

227
00:16:45,360 --> 00:16:48,240
- But that's not easy to do.
- Yes.

228
00:16:49,098 --> 00:16:53,148
Wait. We have a professional
household searcher here.

229
00:17:31,396 --> 00:17:34,396
Without libido, we are no longer men.

230
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:37,010
But at the same time,
it can be a hassle.

231
00:17:37,874 --> 00:17:40,134
It's not easy being a man.

232
00:17:41,156 --> 00:17:43,446
This is as precious
as a national treasure.

233
00:17:45,861 --> 00:17:46,691
Wait.

234
00:17:48,721 --> 00:17:49,971
What is this?

235
00:17:52,883 --> 00:17:54,963
And found something?

236
00:18:02,567 --> 00:18:03,407
What is it?

237
00:18:13,774 --> 00:18:14,734
What the...?

238
00:18:15,273 --> 00:18:19,016
Shunga, another name for
Ukiyoe artwork on human Eros.

239
00:18:19,016 --> 00:18:23,563
Also called Funny Pictures, used as a
talisman to protect someone from evil.

240
00:18:23,564 --> 00:18:27,201
In the old custom, it was given
to a bride as an educational material

241
00:18:27,202 --> 00:18:30,814
to prevent her from being surprised
on her bridal night.

242
00:18:34,096 --> 00:18:37,386
I think my mother brought these
with her when she got married.

243
00:18:40,281 --> 00:18:41,781
This must be it.

244
00:18:44,068 --> 00:18:47,869
As soon as we found them, I took them
to our family temple for the service.

245
00:18:48,090 --> 00:18:49,840
Then her ghost never came back.

246
00:18:52,154 --> 00:18:56,574
Why did she remember them now
long after her death?

247
00:18:57,470 --> 00:19:01,190
That's because her son was worried
about his porn DVDs.

248
00:19:01,679 --> 00:19:03,889
That must have
reminded her about her own.

249
00:19:06,319 --> 00:19:07,923
My mother is like me.

250
00:19:08,118 --> 00:19:10,118
She can't throw away anything.

251
00:19:10,903 --> 00:19:12,243
It's our frugal mentality.

252
00:19:12,512 --> 00:19:14,852
She was worried about you.

253
00:19:16,387 --> 00:19:19,977
Your mother.
She saw you acting so lonely.

254
00:19:20,601 --> 00:19:23,441
So, she came back
to urge you to find someone.

255
00:19:24,342 --> 00:19:26,932
Whether she is in the afterlife
or in this world,

256
00:19:27,251 --> 00:19:28,461
she is your parent.

257
00:19:28,622 --> 00:19:30,162
And you are always her son.

258
00:19:36,119 --> 00:19:37,789
Have a drink, everyone.

259
00:19:38,739 --> 00:19:40,829
It's on me today.

260
00:19:41,002 --> 00:19:43,728
Lucky us!

261
00:19:58,887 --> 00:20:00,097
Hello.

262
00:20:00,581 --> 00:20:01,501
Welcome.

263
00:20:03,135 --> 00:20:04,225
You look great.

264
00:20:06,285 --> 00:20:08,155
Luckily, yes.

265
00:20:09,838 --> 00:20:11,178
I'm Okubo, the nurse.

266
00:20:14,042 --> 00:20:16,502
Right. Thank you for taking care of me.

267
00:20:17,661 --> 00:20:20,464
I didn't recognize you
without your nurse uniform.

268
00:20:20,474 --> 00:20:21,934
People tell me that a lot.

269
00:20:23,553 --> 00:20:24,803
How are you feeling?

270
00:20:25,968 --> 00:20:30,298
As you can see, I've gotten much better
like I was born a new person.

271
00:20:32,967 --> 00:20:35,177
What brings you here today?

272
00:20:35,423 --> 00:20:37,463
I wanted to see your store.

273
00:20:38,653 --> 00:20:41,283
Really? All the way to see the store?

274
00:20:42,553 --> 00:20:44,713
I have been worried about you.

275
00:20:50,319 --> 00:20:51,369
Any recommendations?

276
00:20:55,032 --> 00:20:58,220
Right. How about some okra?

277
00:20:58,522 --> 00:21:01,032
- Sure! I'll take one.
- Just one?

278
00:21:01,033 --> 00:21:03,073
- Then two.
- Two.

279
00:21:12,596 --> 00:21:13,426
Here you go.

280
00:21:16,347 --> 00:21:19,017
Salt determines the flavor of sour plum.

281
00:21:19,306 --> 00:21:22,026
If you use coarse salt with bittern,

282
00:21:22,191 --> 00:21:26,821
not table salt, it enhances
the umami flavor in the plum.

283
00:21:27,962 --> 00:21:30,962
The plums in plum wine can be
eaten as is.

284
00:21:31,605 --> 00:21:33,905
You can also make jam and jelly out of it.

285
00:21:35,298 --> 00:21:36,128
That's it.

286
00:21:37,050 --> 00:21:39,380
Good night.

287
00:21:41,573 --> 00:21:46,119
Yoichi...

288
00:21:47,477 --> 00:21:49,057
You can rest in peace now.

289
00:21:49,915 --> 00:21:52,165
I've found someone special.

290
00:21:52,960 --> 00:21:54,210
Nice to meet you.

291
00:21:54,396 --> 00:21:56,736
I will take care of his health.

292
00:21:58,016 --> 00:21:59,936
I will take over making sour plums.

293
00:22:01,603 --> 00:22:02,683
And...

294
00:22:02,819 --> 00:22:05,699
I'll take good care of
your Shunga. Mother.

295
00:22:14,507 --> 00:22:16,673
- Rest in peace.
- Rest in peace.

296
00:23:40,921 --> 00:23:45,890
THIS STORY IS FICTION

